  21 Nov 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  nwn-data-1.29-r1.ebuild:
  Fixed my misspelled linguas, and (hopefully) fixed support for the Diamond
  DVD for bug #155831.

*nwn-data-1.29-r1 (17 Nov 2006)

  17 Nov 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  +nwn-data-1.29-r1.ebuild:
  This is the initial import of my new all-encompassing nwn-data ebuild. This
  shoudl support Platinum, Diamond, and the Original sets. It may work with
  Gold, but that hasn't been tested. This is currently masked, as I am
  planning on adding more support, such as support for NWMovies and having
  player data in ~/.nwn, instead of a writeable global NWN directory. This
  should take care of bug #88521, bug #118446, and bug #148791.

  27 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Change the instructions at the end of the ebuild from einfo to elog.

  05 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Fixing package collisions with games-rpg/nwn and closing bug #145593.

  01 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Add some more error checking into the unpacking stage.

  29 Aug 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Stable for games-rpg/nwn-1.6.7-r1+

  29 Jul 2006; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  more download sites and use MY_PV a couple more places - modified patch from
  Andreas Fischer via bug #142040

  05 Jul 2006; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Add bioware d/l location

  03 Jun 2006; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  needs unzip (bug #135338) - reported by Ryan Hill

  31 Mar 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Changed nomirror to mirror and nostrip to strip.

  31 Jan 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  This revision resolves the broken installation that happened after moving
  nwn.png from FILESDIR to DISTFILES.

  23 Jan 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> -files/nwn.png,
  nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Moved nwn.png to DISTDIR.

  05 Jan 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Removing games-rpg/nwn from RDEPEND.

  05 Jan 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Removed dependency on virtual/x11 and added RDEPEND on >=games-rpg/nwn-1.66-r1.

  21 Dec 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Added .metadata directory for possible use in the nwn ebuild.

  02 Nov 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Added license checking.

  01 Nov 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Fixed installation when not using USE=nowin.

  17 Oct 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Added nwmouse check from bug #106789 for bug #109619.

  30 Sep 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Fixed cosmetic errors on USE=-nowin.

  22 Sep 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Added echo lines to inform users which CD they'll need.

*nwn-data-1.29 (21 Sep 2005)

  21 Sep 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> +files/nwn.png,
  +metadata.xml, +nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Initial import. Ebuild by me. This is the first ebuild for breaking up
  Neverwinter Nights into 2 ebuilds. This ebuild also adds support for
  installing the Shadows of Undrentide and Hordes of the Underdark expansion
  packs from CD using USE=sou and USE=hou respectively.

